I"E<p>The <code>sky_hub</code> platform offers presence detection by looking at connected devices to a <a href="https://www.sky.com/shop/broadband-talk/sky-hub/">Sky Hub router</a> based router.</p>
<p>To use your Sky Hub device in your installation, add the following to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
device_tracker:
  - platform: sky_hub
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='host' href='#host'></a> host</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The IP address of your router.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>192.168.1.254</p>
</p></dd></dl>
</div>
<p>See the <a href="/integrations/device_tracker/">device tracker integration page</a> for instructions how to configure the people to be tracked.</p>
